article.headline: Green Bay 86, Long Beach St. 75
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. -- Ryan Tillema scored 30 points to lead the University of Wisconsin-Green Bay to a 86-75 victory over Long Beach State Saturday. Tillema made 10 of 17 shots, including 7 of 10 3-pointers as the Phoenix (21-8) improved to 9-0 this season when scoring over 80 points. Tillema scored 20 of his 30 points in the first half. He scored 14 points during a 36-14 Green Bay run over an 11 minute span of the first half. The Phoenix increased its lead to 24 points in the second half. The 49ers (13-12) cut the lead to 81-71 on a pair of free throws by TJ Robisnon with 3:08 remaining but couldn't get any closer.
